result.execSummary:
The defendant Jace A. Hannemann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jace A. Hannemann is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jace A. Hannemann was found guilty of Incest with Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.06(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or Substance Abuse Program.  Defendant shall receive credit as listed below.  Sentence shall run consecutive to any other imposed sentence.

miscConds.notes:
Defendant shall submit a payment with amount deemed appropriate by the agent on a monthly basis.
If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

No contact with any victim listed.  No contact with minors without approved chaperone and permission of agent.  No internet use for social media purposes, no sexually explict websites or as restricted by the agent.

Complete compas assessment,  counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate and followup.  Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections and follow rules of supervision.  Submit DNA sample if not previously submitted.  Defendant shall complete research paper on dangers of exposing one's self sexually online-minimum of 6 pages and present to agent and at least two youth organizations while supervised by a chaperone.  Defendant shall complete sex offender treatment.  Defendant shall comply with sex offender registry.
Defendant shall obtain/maintain full-time employment or full-time educations or combination of both.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent to Count #1.  Consecutive to any previously imposed sentence.  Credit for 7 days.

superMiscConds.notes: The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, restitution and surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.   Penalty for non-payment shall be entry of civil judgment.   Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees.  Send payments to:  Clerk of Courts, Room 423, 415 Jackson Street, P O Box 2808, Oshkosh WI  54903-2808.
